Hi @ton31337 , could you please review this patch? 
This is ported from PR FRRouting/frr#20618. 
Regarding the conflict in route_vty_out() , I believe it does not affect the fix, so I keep the code base consistent with 10.4.1 and 10.5.1. 
```
// Definition of route_vty_out() in FRR master
extern void route_vty_out(struct vty *vty, const struct prefix *p, struct bgp_path_info *path,
			  int display, struct attr *attr, safi_t safi, json_object *json_paths,
			  bool wide, char *rd_str);

// Definition of route_vty_out() in frr-10.4.1 and frr-10.5.1
extern void route_vty_out(struct vty *vty, const struct prefix *p, struct bgp_path_info *path,
			  int display, struct attr *attr, safi_t safi, json_object *json_paths,
			  bool wide);

// The code in PR FRRouting/frr#20618
route_vty_out(vty, rn_p, bpi, 0, adj->attr, safi, NULL, wide, NULL);

// This patch keeps the code base aligned with frr-10.4.1 and frr-10.5.1
route_vty_out(vty, rn_p, bpi, 0, adj->attr, safi, NULL, wide);
```
Thanks a lot.

